description: A mixed use development comprising the retention of 5,635 sq m of existing office accommodation in Bromyard House; the change of use and conversion of the remainder of Bromyard House and roof addition to form 478 residential units (52 x studio apartments, 180 x one bed apartments, 239 x 2 bed apartments, 7 x 3 bed apartments) and 15 live/work units; the erection of three 3 storey buildings forming 27 residential units (27 x 2 bed apartments); the erection of a 3 storey building forming 21 residential units (21 x 3 bed apartments); served by 380 parking spaces (330 residential and 50 office); erection of 4,659 sq m office building, served by 71 car parking spaces; landscaping and associated works
decision_conditions: The development permitted shall be begun before the expiration of five years from the date of this permission.  REASON:	In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990. | The development shall be carried out in accordance with a phasing programme to be approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and the development shall not be carried out other than in accordance with this programme.  REASON: To ensure a satisfactory form and sequence of development is achieved in accordance with adopted UDP policy B1 & P2 and RUDP policy 4.1 & 1.10. | Noise mitigation measures set out in paragraphs 6.51 - 6.61 (p.36-37) of the EIA and details of mitigation measures in respect of air quality as contained in the EIA, shall be provided in accordance with the details so approved, before of any part of the development is occupied and retained permanently with regular maintenance of the proposed equipment.  REASON: To ensure that this essential aspect of the development is carried out prior to the use or occupation of any part of the development to secure a satisfactory living environment in accordance with adopted and replacement UDP policies B8 and 4.11. | Samples of the materials to be used for the external surfaces of the development including:- (i) The new 3-storey blocks of flats to the north of the site; (ii) The new terrace of flats in Third Avenue; (iii) The proposed roof extension and to Bromyard House; (iv) The new entrances to Bromyard House; (v) Surface finishes to childrens' play area, cycle storage areas, car parking and accesses; shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before any part of the relevant development is commenced, and this condition shall apply notwithstanding any indications as to these matters which have been given in this application. Development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details.   REASON: To ensure that the materials harmonise with the surroundings, in accordance with adopted UDP policies B1 and B5 and RUDP policy 4.1. | For each phase identified pursuant to condition no. 2 no development shall take place until full details of both hard and soft landscape works, including a phased programme of works and an accurate tree survey indicating condition, size and spread etc. for whole site and spread of trees from Bromyard Ave etc, indicating which trees are to be retained and which removed, have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and these works shall be carried out as approved prior to the occupation of any phase of the development or in accordance with the programme agreed by the Local Planning Authority. Any trees or other plants which die or are removed within the first five years following the implementation of the landscaping scheme shall be replaced during the next planting season.   REASON: To ensure that the development is landscaped in the interests of the visual character and appearance of the area in accordance with adopted UDP policies B2 and ES4 and RUDP policy 4.5. | Prior to the occupation of the relevant phase of the development a schedule of landscape maintenance for a minimum period of 5 years has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The schedule shall include details for the arrangement of its implementation. Landscape maintenance shall be carried out in accordance with the approved schedule.   REASON: To protect the landscaping in the interests of the visual character and appearance of the area in accordance with adopted UDP policies B2, ES4 and RUDP policies 4.5. | For each phase identified pursuant to condition no. 2 no development shall take place until there has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority a plan including the positions, design, materials and type of boundary treatment to be erected and an implementation programme. Development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details.   REASON: To protect the visual appearance of the area and the living conditions of neighbouring occupiers in accordance with adopted UDP policies B1, B2 and RUDP policies 4.1 and 4.5. | The entire root system of trees to be retained, as shown on the approved drawings, indicated by the  spread of their branches, shall be protected by stout exclusion fencing until completion of the  development.  REASON: To prevent damage to the trees in the interest of the visual character and appearance of the  Area in accordance with adopted UDP policies B2, ES4 and RUDP policies 4.5. | The area beneath the spread of the branches of the trees to be retained as shown on the approved  drawings shall not be used for the storage of building materials, plant, machinery or other items, or for  vehicular access or for the burning of materials of any kind.  REASON: To prevent damage to the trees in the interest of the visual character and appearance of the  Area in accordance with adopted policies B2, ES4 and RUDP policies 4.5. | Prior to commencement of work on the relevant phase of the development as identified pursuant to condition no. 2, on site dustbin and enclosed refuse areas, details of which shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority, shall be sited a maximum distance of 23 metres (10 metres where paladins are employed) from an adopted highway, and a maximum of 25 metres from any dwelling unit intended to use them.   REASON: To comply with the Council's Design Guides in accordance with adopted UDP policy H34 and RUDP policies 4.1 and 5.5. | The communal garden areas as shown on the approved site plan (Drawing No. BHB PL-100) shall be retained permanently for communal use of the residents of the development. No walls or fences or other means of enclosure, other than those shown on the approved drawings, shall be erected within or around these garden areas, unless otherwise approved by the Local Planning Authority, and thereafter carried out as approved.  REASON: To ensure that a uniform design and appearance to the street scene is retained in the interests of the visual amenity of the area; and in order to secure a safe environment in accordance with adopted policies B2 and ES4 and RUDP policy 4.5. | Notwithstanding the details shown on the drawings the northern boundary wall to the car park and podium blocks shall be faced in solid brickwork with no openings or grilles and thereafter so maintained unless otherwise agreed in writing with the Local Planning Authority  REASON: To protect the living conditions of the neighbouring residential properties in accordance with adopted policies B2 and ES4 and RUDP policy 4.5. | Details of all external lighting to be erected including new lights at roof level, demonstrating compliance with the recommendations of the Institution of Lighting Engineers "Guidance Notes for the Reduction of Light Pollution" and the provisions of BS5489 Part 9, must be submitted in writing to and approved by the Local Planning Authority prior to the development commencing. The lighting as approved must be installed prior to the first occupation of any part of the development and maintained in accordance with these standards thereafter.   REASON: To protect the living conditions of occupiers of the area in accordance with adopted policies B5 and ES5 and RUDP policies 4.1 and 4.5. | Details of Police Secured by Design Measures, including investigation into the provision of (i) automated barrier controls to each entrance to the underground car parking, (ii) lighting within the site, including in the underground parking areas (iii) re-location of cycle storage facilities within Bromyard House and  (iv) CCTV submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and the approved details implemented prior to first occupation of the relevant part of the development and thereafter permanently retained.   REASON: To ensure that the proposed development achieves the required crime prevention elements as detailed by the Government Circular 5/94 'Planning Out Crime' and with requirements of clause 17 of the Crime and Disorder Act 1988 which imposes a duty on a Local Authority 'to do all that it can to prevent crime and disorder in its area' in accordance with adopted UDP policy B20 and RUDP policies 4.3 & 4.4. | The construction of the site drainage system shall be carried out in accordance with details set out by the Environment Agency, which shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before development commences unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.  REASON:  To prevent pollution of the water environment in accordance with adopted UDP policy R10 and RUDP policy 2.5. | The use of the new 3-storey office building for Department of Pensions and Works purposes, shall not be open to visiting members of the public outside 08.30 hours to 16.30 hours Monday to Friday and not at any time on Saturday, Sundays or Bank or Public Holidays.   REASON: In the interests of the living conditions of occupiers of nearby properties in accordance with adopted UDP policies B5 and ES5 and RUDP policy 4.1 & 4.11. | Any machinery audible outside the premises shall be designed to an acoustic standard not  exceeding Noise Rating NR35 measured or calculated at the nearest horizontal or vertical boundary of the nearest affected dwelling, whichever is the closer, and implemented in accordance with this standard at first installation and permanently retained.  REASON: To protect the living conditions of neighbouring occupiers in accordance with adopted UDP policy B5 and RUDP policy 4.1. | Suitable and sufficient acoustic separation to at least that specified in the 1992 Edition of the  Approved Document E of the Building Regulations 1991 shall be provided between (i) the ceilings  and walls of the new live/work units at ground floor and adjoining residential units on the ground  and first floors, (ii) the  adjoining live/work units at ground floor and the residential units at second floor, (iii) the ceilings  and walls of the offices at ground to third floors and residential units at ground to fourth  floors, (iv) the ceilings of the parking decks and the basement and ground floors of the new 3-storey  blocks of flats on the north boundary of the site. Such measures shall be implemented prior to first  occupation of the relevant part of the development.    REASON:   To protect the living conditions of the adjacent occupiers in accordance with adopted UDP policy B5 and RUDP policy 4.1. | No part of the residential development or retained office accommodation hereby permitted shall be occupied or brought into use until the existing accesses to the site from Third Avenue and Bromyard Avenue, have been permanently closed.   REASON: In the interests of highway safety in accordance with adopted UDP policies T62 and RUDP policies 9.1 and 9.5. | No part of the residential development or retained office accommodation hereby permitted shall be occupied or brought into use until the new access on Bromyard Avenue has been constructed.  REASON: In the interests of highway safety in accordance with adopted UDP policies T62 and RUDP policies 9.1 and 9.5. | Prior to the commencement of the relevant phase of the development identified pursuant to condition no. 2 copies of Drawings Nos. BHB PL-100/B & 101/D shall be submitted for approval identifying the areas of parking to be used in conjunction with the residential and retained office elements. The car parking spaces shown on the plans thus approved shall be provided on site prior to the first occupation of the relevant part of the development. These spaces shall thereafter only be used separately in conjunction with the identified user and shall not be used for any other purpose without the prior permission in writing of the Local Planning Authority.  REASON: To ensure that there is adequate provision for car parking within the site in accordance with adopted UDP policies T40 and T56 and RUDP policy 9.1. | Before any works commence on the residential and retained office element of the scheme, details of pedestrian access scheme within the site, in accordance with standards shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. Development shall be carried out in accordance with approved details and thereafter permanently retained.    REASON: To provide adequate facilities for pedestrians and in the interests of sustainable  Development in accordance with adopted UDP policies T62 and RUDP policies 9.1 & 9.5. | Prior to first occupation of the dwellings, details of a hedge 'buffer' to provide private garden space  for the proposed ground floor flats in Third Avenue shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Development shall be carried out in accordance with approved details and thereafter permanently retained.  REASON: In the interests of the living conditions of future occupiers of the flats in accordance with adopted policies B1, B2 and RUDP policies 4.1 and 4.5. | The 184 units of affordable accommodation hereby approved shall be permanently retained on site and shall not be used for any other purpose, including private tenure, without the prior approval  in writing by the Local Planning Authority.  REASON: To ensure that an acceptable amount of affordable housing is maintained within the development, in accordance with UDP policy H4 and RUDP policy 5.2. | No development shall take place until full details of sustainable development measures including details of:- (i) proposed domestic waste and water recycling, (ii) proposed electric cars and any other measures aimed at reducing the need to travel, (iii) promotion of use of alternative fuels by commercial occupants who are vehicle operators, (iv) provisions to enhance the indoor quality of commercial and residential buildings, such as appropriate design of heating/ventilation/filtration systems to ensure that the impact of poor external air quality is minimised and all-electric dwellings, (v) composting, (vi) lighting and the use of natural energy and (vii) full use of landscaping to provide a buffer between the roads and dwellings have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Such proposals are to be implemented in accordance with the details so approved and will be subject to review every three years thereafter.   REASON: In the interests of sustainability and air quality improvements in accordance with the Council's sustainable development policies. | Details of a Green Travel Plan to minimise car travel to the site shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local planning Authority and implemented prior to first occupation and shall continue to operate thereafter. The Green Travel Plan will be reviewed every three years thereafter.  REASON: In the interests of sustainability and to minimise noise and disturbance to neighbours in accordance with the Council's sustainable development policies and RUDP 9.1. | No external plant or machinery shall be permitted except in accordance with an approval of  details by the Local Planning Authority through the submission of a planning application.   REASON: To protect the living conditions of occupiers of neighbouring properties in accordance with adopted UDP policies B5 and RUDP policies 4.1. | Prior to the first occupation of the residential element full details of the distribution of car parking Spaces for occupiers of the private and affordable units shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The details as approved shall be brought into use prior to the first occupation of any part of the development permitted and retained permanently.  REASON: To ensure that there is an acceptable distribution of parking spaces for all occupiers of the new development in accordance with policies T40 and T56 and RUDP policy 9.1. | Prior to commencement of the relevant  phase identified pursuant to condition no. 2 details shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority in respect of disabled access within and into the buildings shown in this application; such details shall include details of:-   (i) Level accesses to and within all residential buildings, including internal manoeuvring space in all principal rooms, bathrooms and toilets; (ii) Level accesses to and within the new office block and provision of accessible shower and changing facilities (iii)        the design, layout and material of all amenity and landscaped areas;  shall be carried out prior to first occupation of any dwellings and thereafter permanently retained as approved. This condition shall apply notwithstanding the information contained in the application.  REASON: To provide appropriate accessibility for people with disabilities in accordance with adopted UDP policies B1, ES3 & H12 and RUDP policies 4.1, 4.3 & 5.3. | Details of the laying out and location of the child's play area, shown on the submitted layout plans Drawing Nos. BHB PL-100/B, shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority before any works commence on site on the residential part of the development and the play area shall be provided in accordance with the details so approved before any part of the residential development is occupied and retained  permanently.  REASON: To ensure satisfactory development and provision of play facilities in accordance with adopted UDP policy H32. | On site vehicle speed limit shall be no more than 10 mph, details of this and traffic management measures internal to the site, including timing of implementation, shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority prior to commencement of works and shall be implemented in accordance with the approved details and timing, and shall be permanently retained.  REASON: In the interests of pedestrian safety in accordance with adopted UDP policy T62 and RUDP policy 9.1 & 9.5. | Prior to first occupation of the development, full details of the height and the position of the Proposed roof top screen including proposed sight lines shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details and thereafter permanently retained.   REASON: To protect the living conditions of occupiers in the area in accordance with the adopted UDP policies B5 & H33 and RUDP policies 4.1 and 5.5. | Prior to commencement of the relevant phase identified pursuant to condition no. 2, full details of the layout of the proposed live/work units shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority in writing. Development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details and thereafter permanently retained. No alterations to the internal layout of each live/work unit and no use of each live/work unit for full residential use shall be carried out without the prior permission of the Local Planning Authority, obtained through the submission of a planning application.    REASON: To maintain an appropriate mix of uses on the site in accordance with adopted residential and employment UDP and RUDP policies. | The proposed dining room windows in the north elevation of the podium blocks shall only contain obscure glass. A sample of the obscured glass, no smaller than 300 mm square shall be submitted and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before any work is commenced on the relevant part of the development, and the development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the sample thus approved. The details so approved shall be retained permanently.  REASON: To protect the living conditions of neighbouring properties in accordance with adopted policy B5 and RUDP policy 4.1. | Surface water drainage works shall be carried out in accordance with details which shall have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before development commences.  REASON: To prevent the increased risk of flooding, in accordance with Adopted UDP policy R10 and RUDP 2.5 | Surface water source control measures shall be carried out in accordance with details which shall have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before development commences.  REASON: To prevent the increased risk of flooding and improve water quality, in accordance with Adopted UDP policy R10 and RUDP 2.5
